To convert the concentration of H+ from moles per liter (mol/L) to moles per liter (mol/L), we divide 0.01 by 0.00001. Therefore, the number of H+ ions in the solution is 0.00000000001 and the number of acid molecules in the solution is 1, which means the acid solution has a pH of 7.2.
